  "body": "There are three things that bother me about the Sign Message feature:\r\n\r\nThe first I see as a bug:\r\n\r\n1. It's in the footer with a static URL to `https://www.mycrypto.com/signmsg.html` this prevents users who download MyCrypto and run it locally from running that feature locally. However, the `signmsg.html` is part of the local download copy so there's no reason to not use a relative URL?\r\n\r\nThe second is an oddity but I don't think it actually matters:\r\n\r\n2. When you load the page it appears to always connect to `mycryptoapi.com` even if you previously had another node selected. I don't think being connected to a node matters at all for this function/feature so perhaps this is a non-issue.\r\n\r\nThe 3rd I see more as a feature request ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\n3. The \"Verify Message\" function is just a big text box that requires a pre-formatted JSON. I think it would be cool to have a field input option similar to `https://etherscan.io/verifySig` to make it a little more user friendly.",
